<?php include "../header/header.php"; ?><html><body><div class="container"><br><h1>Java Array Split</h1><br><br>We can split array into two parts in Java using the split() method.<br><br><b>Syntax:</b> <br><code>split(String regularExpression);</code><br><br>> split() returns the <b>array of string values</b> which contains values after splitting this string around matches of the given regular expression.<br><hr><br><b>Example:</b><br><code><br>String bi="1101101111101";<br>String arr[]=bi.split("0");<br></code><br><b>output:</b> arr=[11,11,11111,1]</div></body></html><br><br><?php include "../footer/footer.php"; ?>